<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="294" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/865</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A joint commission of Senators and Deputies has been appointed to
                            investigate railroad matters. Mr. Norton will present railroad’s case to
                            the commission. He informs me that the new administration seems to be
                            friendly.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Belden</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>